:[{"name":"Merrigan","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Eamon.","Irish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó Muireagáin</b> ‘descendant of <i>Muireagán</i>’ a personal name derived from <i>muir</i> ‘sea’. Compare   Morgan  , with which this name has been confused."]},{"name":"Morgans","meanings":["Welsh (especially Glamorgan): variant of   Morgan  , with post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>."]}]},{"name":"Jonet","type":"FIRST","meanings":["A Scottish form of Janet."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Verch","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Otto, Orlo.","German: variant of   Ferch  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Ferch","meanings":["German: variant of   Ferg  . Compare   Verch  .","Probably also an Americanized form of German <b>Förtsch</b> (see   Foertsch  ).","Probably also an Americanized form of German <b>Förch</b> (see   Foerch  )."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Jonet Verch Morgan was born in 1134, in Maenclochog, Pembrokeshire, Wales, United Kingdom, her father, Morgan ap Hywell, was 35 and her mother, Mrs. Morgan ap Hywel, was 31. She married Prince Maelgwn of Maelienydd about 1169, in Radnorshire, Wales. They were the parents of at least 3 sons. She died about 1177, in Kerry, Montgomeryshire, Wales, United Kingdom, at the age of 44."},"et":{"1134–about 1177":"1134–umbes 1177","1134–1177":"1134–1177","1150–1197":"1150–1197","1169–Male":"1169–Surnud","1174–1234":"1174–1234","1177–Male":"1177–Surnud","1100–Male":"1100–Surnud","1104–Female":"1104–Surnud","1104":"1104","1169":"1169","1234":"1234","1134":"1134","1100":"1100","1177":"1177","about 1169":"umbes 1169","1197":"1197","1174":"1174","1150":"1150","about 1177":"umbes 1177","about 1174":"umbes 1174","Radnorshire, Wales":"Radnorshire, Wales","Kerry, Montgomeryshire, Wales, United Kingdom":"Kerry, Montgomeryshire, Wales, United Kingdom","Wales":"Wales","Maelienydd, Radnorshire, Wales":"Maelienydd, Radnorshire, Wa